    <h2> Exploring Articial Intelligence</h2>
      <h3>Exploring Artificial Intelligence</h3>
      <p>
        Following the rapid advancements in AI, understanding its operations and applications is important. Artificial Intelligence is designed to emulate human intelligence. It enables machines to learn, adapt to new inputs, and execute tasks usually requiring human intellect (Martie et al., 2023). One significant branch of AI is Natural Language Processing (NLP). NLP allows AI to understand and generate human language. It acts as a conduit between humans and computers, facilitating more intuitive interactions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Take the educational sector as an example. In this case, AI using NLP can examine a large number of course reviews. It discerns student sentiments and organises feedback into distinct topics, such as the quality of course content or instructor performance. This process employs advanced models like BERT and RoBERTa. These models explore the contextual meanings of words, providing a nuanced understanding of text (Koufakou, 2023).
      </p>
      <p>
        NLP involves various techniques. Sentiment analysis is one, determining the emotional tone behind words to gain an understanding of the attitudes, opinions, and emotions expressed. It classifies the sentiments in the text as positive, negative, or neutral. Another technique, named entity recognition, identifies and categorises entities in the text, such as names of persons, organisations, or locations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Additionally, keyword search and topic modelling are also integral components of NLP. They enable AI to filter through textual data, extract pertinent information, and identify patterns. These techniques can also be used to visualise the derived insights. Thus, AI is not merely a conceptual framework. It is a practical tool actively used to extract meaningful insights from textual data, reshaping our interaction and understanding of information (Koufakou, 2023).
      </p>
      <h4>Role of Deep Learning in Text Analysis</h4>
      <p>
        Deep learning remains essential in text analysis, serving as the foundation for advanced AI models and changing the approach towards understanding and interpreting textual data. This technology helps find detailed patterns and important insights from large amounts of text, outperforming older models that need manual setup to look for specific features. Especially in neural networks, deep learning models learn these features autonomously. Innovations in architectures, such as Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) and transformers, have been instrumental in advancing the comprehension of context and semantics in textual data, fostering the development of more nuanced and contextually aware AI models (Gruetzemacher & Paradice, 2021).
      </p>
